Description: Integrates concepts of stochastic demography into species
    distribution modelling. The main approach is maximize the likelihood function
    with environmental information from the presence/absence. This inference can
    be used to project species geographic range.
    Data requirements include species detection records and spatiotemporal
    environmental data.
